<paragraph id="830D3687FFE40636FB09E995781B5A7D" blockId="30.[809,1426,398,1061]" pageId="30" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE40636FB09E99579335FFB" box="[809,1073,398,420]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="585">Diagnosis (emended):</emphasis>
Short body, dorsoventrally flattened, up to 21 segments. Prostomium bilobed. Frontal filaments present (
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE40636FCA0E9D4788A5FBB" authorityName="* Pettibone" authorityYear="1976" box="[1152,1416,462,483]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyfauvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="30" pageNumber="585" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE40636FCA0E9D4788A5FBB" box="[1152,1416,462,483]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="585">Bathyfauvelia affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or absent (
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE40636FB97E9F479EE5C5B" authority="Bonifácio &amp; Menot, 2019" authorityName="Bonifácio &amp; Menot" authorityYear="2019" box="[951,1260,494,515]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyfauvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="30" pageNumber="585" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="glacigena" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE40636FB97E9F479EE5C5B" box="[951,1260,494,515]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="585">Bathyfauvelia glacigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="AAF557EEFFE40636FCD8E9F578555C5C" box="[1272,1367,495,516]" pageId="30" pageNumber="585" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE40636FB09EA1479315C7C" authority="Bonifácio &amp; Menot, 2019" authorityName="Bonifácio &amp; Menot" authorityYear="2019" box="[809,1075,526,548]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyfauvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="30" pageNumber="585" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ignigena" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE40636FB09EA1479315C7C" box="[809,1075,526,548]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="585">Bathyfauvelia ignigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="AAF557EEFFE40636FC1AEA1579935C7C" box="[1082,1169,527,548]" pageId="30" pageNumber="585" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). Eyes absent. Median antenna present, lateral antennae absent. Facial tubercle absent. Tentaculophores with acicula and chaetae. Pharynx with two pairs of jaws; serrated margins with nine pairs of pharyngeal papillae. Dorsal tubercles forming cirriform to lamelliform branchiallike processes. Elytrophores large, up to nine pairs, on segments 2, 4, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13, 15 and 17. Parapodia subbiramous, notopodia shorter than neuropodia; noto- and neuropodia with elongate acicular lobe; tips of noto- and neuroaciculae not penetrating epidermis. Notochaetae stout, distally with spinous rows; notochaetae stouter than neurochaetae. Neurochaetae distally flattened to concave, serrated along both margins. From segment 3, ventral cirri inserted medially on neuropodia. Nephridial papillae present, small. Pygidium rounded, with dorsal anus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="830D3687FFE40636FB09EC557E6B587E" blockId="30.[809,1426,1103,1574]" pageId="30" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE40636FB09EC557E9B5A3C" box="[809,921,1103,1124]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="585">Remarks:</emphasis>
The diagnosis of genus 
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE40636FCE9EC5578715A3C" authorityName="Pettibone" authorityYear="1976" box="[1225,1395,1103,1124]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyfauvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="30" pageNumber="585" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE40636FCE9EC5578715A3C" box="[1225,1395,1103,1124]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="585">Bathyfauvelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is emended to include characters observed in the new species described below. These include: absence of frontal filaments and presence of serrated jaws. 
<bibRefCitation id="E7234B76FFE40636FB09ECCA7EEA5ABD" author="Pettibone MH" box="[809,1000,1231,1254]" pageId="30" pageNumber="585" refId="ref56082" refString="Pettibone MH. 1976. Revision of the genus Macellicephala McIntosh and the subfamily Macellicephalinae Hartmann- Schroder (Polychaeta: Polynoidae). Washington: Smithsonian Institution Press." type="book" year="1976">Pettibone (1976)</bibRefCitation>
considered valid only two species in this genus, but a few inconsistencies were observed from the drawings of the Arctic and Mediterranean specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="44B24D04FFE40636FBE8ED2A79C05B1D" authorityName="* Pettibone" authorityYear="1976" box="[968,1218,1328,1349]" class="Polychaeta" family="Polynoidae" genus="Bathyfauvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="30" pageNumber="585" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="B1C6EA95FFE40636FBE8ED2A79C05B1D" box="[968,1218,1328,1349]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="585">Bathyfauvelia affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E7234B76FFE40636FCF3ED2A7E6D5B3E" author="Pettibone MH" pageId="30" pageNumber="585" refId="ref56082" refString="Pettibone MH. 1976. Revision of the genus Macellicephala McIntosh and the subfamily Macellicephalinae Hartmann- Schroder (Polychaeta: Polynoidae). Washington: Smithsonian Institution Press." type="book" year="1976">Pettibone, 1976: 36–37</bibRefCitation>
, figs 21, 22). The specimen from the Arctic Basin shows an elongated acicular lobe in the tentacular segment without chaetae and shorter prostomium lobes, whereas the specimen from the Mediterranean Sea shows a shorter acicular lobe in the tentacular segment with chaetae and slightly longer prostomium lobes.
</paragraph>
